p/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1473_0.4.0.xml#_d2c89488-8a36-464b-94f6-a91d0f5a6c9c" id="_959db499-44bc-414c-af66-4394613f0065" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">sole-occupancy unit</xref> of a Class 2 building or Class 4 part of a building must not exceed the <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/6200_0.5.0.xml#_388e9c95-9236-466e-95b8-ac0bff65dd3d" id="_5e233a0c-dafa-40df-8d65-170acc260624" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="abcb-glossentry">energy value</xref> with—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_5f5a5794-562f-4633-89c8-f1f96b59e9d6">a 3-star ducted heat pump, rated under the 2019 GEMS determination, heating all spaces that are provided with heating; and</li><li id="_344a137b-c3fb-48e0-b5a8-7b8540982010">a 3-star ducted heat pump, rated under the 2019 GEMS determination, cooling all spaces that are provided with cooling; and</li><li id="_2e3424a0-ef15-4f85-a4e7-fa10149df049">a 5-star instantaneous gas water heater, rated under the 2017 GEMS determination, providing all domestic hot water; and</li><li id="_83f15932-3210-445c-90da-c588039b2ae3">a lighting power density of 4 W/m<sup xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" id="_47270384-a434-4325-a7b6-a034b745e0db" inv:access="external">2</sup> serving all internal spaces that are provided with artificial lighting.</li></ol></subclause><subclause id="_54c13eb3-7154-41e1-9966-d14f144ed74f" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_256f294b-0331-4bf8-bbb6-a92f0a2c5a2a">SubClause</title><num>2</num><p><xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" xmlns:qxa="urn:schemas-quark-com:xmlauthor" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1248_1.7.0.xml#_8c00ddfa-fcb3-4339-8101-5c10cd547722" id="_ba9ad314-7910-45c5-99c6-13fbfba076e1" inv:access="external" qxa:read-only="true" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="true" type="glossterm">Domestic services</xref>, including any associated distribution system and components must, to the degree necessary, have features that facilitate the efficient use of energy appropriate to—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_75d78da1-7eee-4c70-98e3-c0adcdf3038f">the <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1248_1.7.0.xml#_8c00ddfa-fcb3-4339-8101-5c10cd547722" id="_83092c96-4fd9-41ef-b789-7b2a3b3e4f9b" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">domestic service</xref> and its usage; and</li><li id="_03258ad4-96b5-4973-be3f-2de1c7819273">the geographic location of the building; and</li><li id="_edf73785-096b-4bac-8ff1-86591dec69a0">the location of the <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/5e2c1f63-e589-4ce1-95e8-5c3e286a7aff/1248_1.7.0.xml#_8c00ddfa-fcb3-4339-8101-5c10cd547722" id="_551c3bf3-6338-480b-a75d-6a83bee625b0" inv:access="external" referencetype="Text" scope="local" synctargettext="false" type="glossterm">domestic service</xref>; and</li><li id="_adc82ba7-3697-4aa5-b19a-a64c210e1189">the energy source.</li></ol></subclause></clause>